        "text": "Hebrews 6:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 10:33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the readers had already exercised this virtue before, and were still exercising it. Yet in their case, since they had become doubtful regarding the absolute truth of Christianity, and in part already sought to withdraw from the outward fellowship of Christians (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 10:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and, moreover, in particularistic prejudice closed their hearts against a brotherly intercourse with the Gentile Christians, the renewed inculcation of this virtue was of special importance.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 13:1-25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Concluding exhortations partly of a general nature, partly in special relation to the main purport of the epistle, and concluding notices, followed by a twofold wish of blessing.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 13:1-6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Exhortations to social manifestations of their Christianity. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ἡ φιλαδελφία μενέτω",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". “Let love of the brethren continue”; it existed (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 6:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") and so, as Chrys. says, he does not write ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Γίνεσθε φιλάδελφοι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀλλὰ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μενέτω ἡ φιλ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". In the general decay of their faith tendencies to disown Christian fellowship had become apparent, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 10:24-25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This might also lead to a failure to recognise the wants of Christians coming from a distance, therefore hospitality is urged; not as a duty they did not already practise, but, gently, as that which they might omit through forgetfulness and as that which might bring them a message from God: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τῆς φιλοξενίας μὴ ἐπιλανθάνεσθε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “Entertainment of strangers do not neglect; for thus some have entertained angels unawares,” as in Genesis 18-19; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jdg 6:11-24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jdg 13:2-23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [For testimonies to the hospitality of Christians Bleek refers to Lucian, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "De Morte Peregrin.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", chap. 16 and to the 49th Epistle of Julian. On the hospitality of the East see Palgrave’s ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Essays",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", p. 246–7.] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἔλαθόν τινες ξενίσαντες",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " though a common classical idiom, occurs nowhere else in the N.T. Some of their fellow Christians might be in even more needy circumstances and therefore.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Let brotherly love continue",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Not only was “brotherly love” (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Philadelphia",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") a new and hitherto almost undreamed of virtue but it was peculiarly necessary among the members of a bitterly-persecuted sect. Hence all the Apostles lay constant stress upon it (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 12:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Thessalonians 4:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Peter 1:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 3:14-18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c.). It was a special form of the more universal “Love” (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ἀγάπη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and our Lord had said that by it the world should recognise that Christians were His disciples (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 13:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). How entirely this prophecy was fulfilled we see alike from the fervid descriptions of tertullian, from the mocking admissions of Lucian in his curious and interesting tract “on the death of Peregrinus,” and from the remark of the Emperor Julian (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ep.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " 49), that their “kindness towards strangers” had been a chief means of propagating their “atheism.” But brotherly-love in the limits of a narrow community is often imperilled by the self-satisfaction of an egotistic and dogmatic orthodoxy, shewing itself in party rivalries. This may have been the case among these Hebrews as among the Corinthians; and the neglect by some of the gatherings for Christian worship (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 10:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") may have tended to deepen the sense of disunion. The disunion however was only incipient, for the writer has already borne testimony to the kindness which prevailed among them (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 6:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 10:32-33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 13:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ἡ φιλαδελφία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "brotherly love",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") The parts of this virtue are unfolded in the sequel. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Paul",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " uses the same word elsewhere.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μενέτω",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "continue",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", although old things have passed away: it does ‘abide’ or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "continue",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (the word of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Paul",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") in itself (as far as concerns itself): ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 13:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 13:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " : ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "let it",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "continue",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " with you (in your case, as far as concerns you).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 1.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Let brotherly love continue.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "Φιλαδελφία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " does not mean general philanthropy, but the peculiar love of Christians to each other as brethren; \"a narrower sphere within the wider sphere of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀγάπη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Delitzsch); cf. 1. Peter 2:17, \"Honor all men, love the brotherhood;\" and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Peter 1:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where Christians are exhorted to add ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀγάπη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " to their ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "φιλαδελπία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This grace of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "φιλαδελφία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " they had already, and had evinced it by their conduct (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 6:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.); they are only to take care that it continue; and let them, among other ways, evince it in hospitality (ver. 2), and in sympathy with the afflicted brethren (ver. 3). Hebrews 13:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Let brotherly love continue (φιλαδελφία μενέτω)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Φιλαδελφία in Paul, Romans 12:10; 1 Thessalonians 4:9. As a proper name, Revelation 1:11; Revelation 3:7. It is not necessary to suppose that the admonition implies signs of estrangement among those addressed. Comp. Hebrews 3:13; Hebrews 6:10; Hebrews 10:24; Hebrews 12:12-15. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Φιλαδελφία in Paul, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Romans 12:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Thessalonians 4:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". As a proper name, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Revelation 1:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Revelation 3:7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". It is not necessary to suppose that the admonition implies signs of estrangement among those addressed. Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Hebrews 3:13",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Hebrews 6:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Hebrews 10:24",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Hebrews 12:12-15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
